<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Teacher Help: Searching for Attendance Records</h1>
        <p><strong>Welcome, Teachers!</strong> This guide will help you navigate the attendance record search feature in the application.</p>

        <h2>How to Search for Attendance Records:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access the Attendance Page:</strong> Navigate to the main dashboard and click on the "Attendance" tab in the navigation menu.</li>
            <li><strong>Search Options:</strong></li>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>By Student Name:</strong> Type the student’s name in the search bar to find their attendance records.</li>
                <li><strong>By Date:</strong> Select a date or date range to filter attendance records.</li>
                <li><strong>By Class:</strong> Use the class filter to view attendance for a specific class.</li>
            </ul>
            <li><strong>Viewing Results:</strong> After entering your search criteria, click the "Search" button to display the records in a table format, including student names, attendance status, and date of attendance.</li>
            <li><strong>Exporting Data:</strong> Click the "Export" button on the results page to export the attendance data in CSV format.</li>
            <li><strong>Help and Support:</strong> If you encounter any issues or need further assistance, contact the school administrator via the support email provided.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>FAQs:</h2>
            <p><strong>Can I search for multiple students at once?</strong> Yes, you can use the search bar to enter multiple student names separated by commas.</p>
            <p><strong>What if the records I’m looking for aren’t showing up?</strong> Ensure that you have selected the correct date range or class. If records are still missing, please contact the administrator.</p>
            <p><strong>Can I print the attendance records?</strong> Yes, there is an option to print the records from the results page.</p>
        </div>

